#eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - South Africa will not be taking sides in the Russia and Ukraine war. This is according to the ANC’s Secretary General Fikile Mbalula who spoke at a briefing on Friday. Mbalula says South Africa has been told to walk away from Russia. READ: ANC serves legal papers on de Ruyter over corruption allegations He says government will not get involved but will advocate for peace. "We're working with everybody, even those who are anti-Russia, to find a solution," says Mbalula. Watch the video above for more details on this story.